memberCommands.name: `/help`
memberCommands.value: This command shows you all the commands you can use

memberCommands.name: `/discordHelp`
memberCommands.value: This command sends you resources to Get Started with Discord

memberCommands.name: `/resources`
memberCommands.value: This command will ping you all the resources you might need for learning Web Development and Design

memberCommands.name: `/jobChallenge`
memberCommands.value: This command provides you informative links for JobChallenge

memberCommands.name: `/socialLinks`
memberCommands.value: This command shows you all the social handles and initiatives of Tanay Pratap

memberCommands.name: `/faq your question`
memberCommands.value:
This command shows the Frequently Asked Question specified by you.
> **Tip:** use specific keywords such as `coding, blogs, etc`

memberCommands.name: `/send @username your message`
memberCommands.value: This command sends a private message to @username specified by you

memberCommands.name: `/serverInfo`
memberCommands.value: This command sends information about the server like no.of members, createdAt, etc

memberCommands.name: `/botInfo`
memberCommands.value: This command sends information about the bot

adminCommands.name: `/kick`
adminCommands.value: This command allows you to kick a @user. Use the command like this `/kick @username`. This command will display an embed on the channel

adminCommands.name: `/prune number`
adminCommands.value: This command deletes the number of messages specified in the `number`. The `number` ranges from 1 to 99. This is command can be used on server channels only, DO NOT USE THIS COMMAND TO DELETE DM MESSAGES.
